  "tutorPrompt": "Topic: Patterns & Sequences. Island: snowy_peaks_island. Difficulty: 5 out of 10. Stage mechanics (1-8): five_tasks, pattern_input, fill_blank, multi_choice, true_false, text_task, corridor_choice, drag_sort. Stage 9: boss_mix.\n\nStage 1 (five_tasks) - Patterns Warm-Up. 5 rounds of 5 quick tasks each about number sequences (what comes next, fill in the gap). Difficulty 5: arithmetic sequences +3 to +15, geometric ×2 and ×3, numbers up to 100.\n\nStage 2 (pattern_input) - Continue the Pattern. Sequences: 4,8,12,16,? | 3,6,9,?,15 | 2,4,8,?,32 | 50,45,?,35,30 | 1,3,9,?,81\n\nStage 3 (fill_blank) - Fill in the Missing Number. Prompts like: 10,15,__,25,30 (+5) | 3,__,12,24 (x2) | 35,28,__,14 (-7) | 3,6,__,12,15 (+3) | 2,6,18,__,162 (x3)\n\nStage 4 (multi_choice) - Odd One Out. Which number breaks the pattern? Sequences where one term does not follow the rule.\n\nStage 5 (true_false) - Is the pattern statement correct? Statements about what comes next or what the rule is.\n\nStage 6 (text_task) - Pattern Word Problems. Story problems about snowballs stacking, yeti footsteps, ice crystals doubling, candles counting, frost core countdown.\n\nStage 7 (corridor_choice) - Which side shows the bigger next number? Compare two sequences side by side.\n\nStage 8 (drag_sort) - Sort numbers in correct ascending or descending sequence order. Items scrambled from sequences like 5,10,15,20,25 or 1,2,4,8,16.\n\nStage 9 (boss_mix) - 16 rounds covering all 8 mechanics (2 per mechanic). Snowy peaks island theme throughout: snowflakes, ice crystals, yeti-monkey Viking, frozen mountain paths.",
